TITLE: Sedgwick Languages Scholarship
INFO: STATUS: Open | APPLICATIONS OPEN: 27/11/2025 | APPLICATIONS CLOSE: 01/04/2026 | VALUE: $5,000.00 | NUMBER OFFERED: 1

[Overview]
The late Dr Enid Sedgwick has provided a bequest to The University of Western Australia (`the University') to provide a travel scholarship to encourage and support a high-achieving Bachelor of Arts student enrolled in French Studies, German Studies, Italian Studies, Spanish Studies, Chinese Studies, Indonesian Studies, Japanese Studies, or Korean Studies at the University.

[Eligibility]
To be eligible for this scholarship applicants must—
(a) be a domestic student;
(b) be enrolled in or intending to enrol in French, German, Italian, Spanish, Chinese, Indonesian, Japanese or Korean Studies honours program at the University; or
(c) have completed at least 48 points towards a Bachelor of Arts prior to the commencement of an approved exchange program;
(d) be enrolled in a Bachelor of Arts with a major in—
(i) French Studies
(ii) German Studies;
(iii) Italian Studies;
(iv) Spanish Studies;
(v) Chinese Studies;
(vi) Indonesian Studies;
(vii) Japanese Studies; or
(viii) Korean Studies;
(e) have applied to undertake a UWA Approved overseas program2 in a country where their language major program is widely spoken.

[Benefits]
The scholarship provides $5,000 to assist the student to travel to a country where the language in their area of study is widely spoken.
